WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.000
No!

00:02.000 --> 00:04.240
OK, everybody.

00:04.240 --> 00:07.440
I want to welcome Harry and his daughter Michelle

00:07.440 --> 00:09.000
to Thanksgiving with him.

00:09.000 --> 00:10.400
Thank you, Dr. Stewart.

00:10.400 --> 00:11.120
Call me, Philip.

00:11.120 --> 00:12.280
OK.

00:12.280 --> 00:15.480
But first, I think we should take a moment and remember

00:15.480 --> 00:17.120
the meaning of Thanksgiving.

00:17.120 --> 00:19.720
Philip, I took Michelle to a school play

00:19.720 --> 00:21.240
about the first Thanksgiving.

00:21.240 --> 00:23.880
Well, I don't you tell us about that, Michelle.

00:23.880 --> 00:27.720
Thanksgiving was about the Pukras, the first settlers in America.

00:27.720 --> 00:29.960
We shared the first harvest of the Indians.

00:29.960 --> 00:31.680
Give up.

00:31.680 --> 00:32.880
All right.

00:32.880 --> 00:36.120
Then in that spirit, let's eat your musk if things.

00:36.120 --> 00:39.720
Each and his own way, who wants to begin.

00:39.720 --> 00:42.000
I will.

00:42.000 --> 00:45.200
I give thanks for being here with my family.

00:45.200 --> 00:48.520
And for being well, so I can enjoy you all.

00:48.520 --> 00:49.560
All right.

00:49.560 --> 00:52.560
We love you, Grandpa.

00:52.560 --> 00:57.160
But I'd like to give thanks for a healthy year.

00:57.160 --> 00:58.920
Good job.

00:58.920 --> 01:01.880
And for meeting Harry and Michelle.

01:01.880 --> 01:04.240
We'd like to give thanks for meeting Susan

01:04.240 --> 01:05.480
and the Stewart family.

01:05.480 --> 01:07.560
I love you, Daddy.

01:07.560 --> 01:08.560
Thanks, Harry.

01:08.560 --> 01:10.280
That was very kind of you.

01:10.280 --> 01:13.920
I'd like to give thanks for Grandpa coming to live with us.

01:13.920 --> 01:16.480
And I'd also like to thank my math teacher for giving me

01:16.480 --> 01:17.840
a passing grade.

01:17.840 --> 01:21.320
And call me, Alexandra.

01:21.320 --> 01:23.280
Oh, my gosh.

01:23.280 --> 01:25.640
You go.

01:25.640 --> 01:27.600
You go first, Marilyn.

01:27.600 --> 01:28.760
I'm thinking you go first.

01:31.760 --> 01:35.640
Well, you all know I'm working on my photo album.

01:35.640 --> 01:37.680
It's not finished yet.

01:37.680 --> 01:41.880
And I'd like to thank Marilyn for being so patient.

01:41.880 --> 01:43.600
Thanks, Richard.

01:43.600 --> 01:45.120
I should thank you for encouraging me

01:45.120 --> 01:47.800
to keep working on my fashion designs.

01:47.800 --> 01:50.160
I'm lucky to have a husband with an artistic eye.

01:50.160 --> 01:52.240
I'm not going to give.

01:52.240 --> 01:54.240
Oh.

01:54.240 --> 01:57.600
We all have a lot to be thankful for.

01:57.600 --> 02:01.160
For the phone on this table, just like the pilgrims.

02:01.160 --> 02:03.320
I'll go along with that, Ellen.

02:03.320 --> 02:05.000
Well, help me, Sarah for Oby.

02:08.960 --> 02:10.480
It was a wonderful meal, Mrs. Stewart.

02:10.480 --> 02:11.160
Thank you.

02:11.160 --> 02:13.280
And now to see the end of the football game.

02:13.280 --> 02:15.080
Exactly.

02:15.080 --> 02:16.880
Where are you going, Philip?

02:16.880 --> 02:18.720
Remember, the Michigan football game

02:18.720 --> 02:21.560
and Michigan needs to touch down.

02:21.560 --> 02:23.120
Did you forget something?

02:23.120 --> 02:25.880
Dad, your famous apple pie.

02:25.880 --> 02:28.080
Just let me see the score, Ellen.

02:28.080 --> 02:29.320
Go ahead, Philip.

02:29.320 --> 02:31.320
You should all take a little break before dessert.

02:31.320 --> 02:33.120
Oh, thank you.

02:33.120 --> 02:34.120
Thank you.

02:34.120 --> 02:35.120
You can prep.

02:35.120 --> 02:37.720
Thank you.

02:37.720 --> 02:38.720
Week.

02:38.720 --> 02:39.520
It's hot.

02:44.520 --> 02:45.400
Who could that be?

02:45.400 --> 02:48.200
Oh, it must be Alexandra.

02:48.200 --> 02:50.320
I invited her to come by for dessert.

02:50.320 --> 02:51.680
You did.

02:51.680 --> 02:52.960
I like Ellen.

02:52.960 --> 02:54.400
You know everyone, Alexandra.

02:54.400 --> 02:57.920
No, she doesn't know Harry Bennett and his daughter, Michelle.

02:57.920 --> 02:58.960
Nice to meet you.

02:58.960 --> 03:00.120
Hi.

03:00.120 --> 03:01.800
Hello, Alex.

03:01.800 --> 03:02.600
Hi, Marilyn.

03:02.600 --> 03:03.280
Hi, Susan.

03:03.280 --> 03:04.480
Happy Thanksgiving.

03:04.480 --> 03:07.040
And Alexandra brought us a pumpkin pie.

03:07.040 --> 03:09.680
Please sit down, Alexandra.

03:09.680 --> 03:10.840
Dad, Richard.

03:10.840 --> 03:14.040
Alexandra's here.

03:14.040 --> 03:15.240
Michigan needs to touch down.

03:15.240 --> 03:16.480
Three minutes to play.

03:16.480 --> 03:17.240
Hi, Alexandra.

03:17.240 --> 03:18.200
Welcome.

03:18.200 --> 03:19.360
Hello, Alexandra.

03:19.360 --> 03:21.160
Yes, Michigan needs to touch down.

03:21.160 --> 03:22.800
One tiny little touchdown.

03:22.800 --> 03:24.320
We just three minutes to play.

03:24.320 --> 03:26.120
You want Michigan to win.

03:26.120 --> 03:27.160
How'd you get?

03:27.160 --> 03:29.920
And Alexandra brought us a pumpkin pie.

03:42.040 --> 03:43.880
What happened?

03:43.880 --> 03:46.760
We forgot to turn the oven on.

03:46.760 --> 03:47.760
Week.

03:49.880 --> 03:52.760
Philip, why don't you go watch the last three minutes

03:52.760 --> 03:57.000
of the game, I will serve coffee and pumpkin pie.

03:57.000 --> 03:58.000
OK.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.720
I'll be back in a few minutes.

04:00.720 --> 04:03.880
Robbie, would you bring the dessert plates and Marilyn?

04:03.880 --> 04:04.800
Would you pour coffee?

04:04.800 --> 04:05.520
Sure, Ellen.

04:09.760 --> 04:12.320
How is your Thanksgiving dinner, Alexandra?

04:12.320 --> 04:14.240
Just wonderful, Mr. Stewart.

04:14.240 --> 04:16.120
The Molinas are a large family.

04:16.120 --> 04:17.720
I love being with them.

04:17.720 --> 04:19.600
I'm glad you came by, Alexandra.

04:19.600 --> 04:20.200
I am, too.

04:23.760 --> 04:27.560
Touch down, touch down, touch down.

04:27.560 --> 04:29.560
Oh, boy.

04:29.560 --> 04:31.520
Great Thanksgiving.

04:31.520 --> 04:34.000
Lots of delightful work.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.200
Michigan scored a touchdown.

04:36.200 --> 04:38.600
Alexandra came by.

04:38.600 --> 04:42.480
And nobody misses Philip's famous apple pie.

04:42.480 --> 04:43.520
Oh, grandpa.

